tool.name: BridgeMovements

param.name: sqsar_layer
param.dialogReference: A layer of Squee-SAR data containing a time series of displacement information. These points can be anywhere on the map, do not need to be contained within bridges only.

param.name: bridge_layer
param.dialogReference: This is a shapefile of all bridges that the user wishes to analyze. The bridges should be added as polygons to the shapefile. All the bridges can be run at once using the tool, or a selection of the bridges can be analyzed.

param.name: warn_thresh
param.displayname: Displacement velocity to use as warning threshold [inch/year]
param.dialogReference: This is a threshold that sets a limit on the maximum amount a point on a bridge should move (on average) over a year. The default warning threshold is 1 inch.

param.name: critical_thresh
param.displayname: Displacement velocity to use as critical threshold [inch/month]
param.dialogReference: This is a threshold that sets a limit on the maximum amount a point on a bridge should move over a month. The default warning threshold is 1/2 an inch.

param.name: out_layer
param.dialogReference: This is the output layer, coloring each bridge according to its condition (RED: CRITICAL, YELLOW: WARNING, GREEN: GOOD.)

tool.summary: This tool detects movement of bridges (sinking or rising) and colors the bridges based on movement beyond normal levels.

dataIdInfo.idAbs: This tool detects movement of bridges (sinking or rising) and colors the bridges based on movement beyond normal levels.
